nd easing the load on application servers and databases. Terracotta uses high-performance mapping of server memory changes, called Network-attached Memory, to share temporary &ldquo;work-in-progress&rdquo; data among servers. That makes an application highly available without placing such temporary data in an expensive relational database. It also provides dramatic cost savings and much higher performance and scalability than either databases or application-tier caches.</p><p>In addition to technical integration, Liferay will bundle Terracotta and serve as a reseller of support.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-ARTICLE', 'IMAGE-FLOW', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20071002091400, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3498, 3499, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3265', 1.0, 'PR-Liferay_China', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content>&lt;div style=\"text-align: center;\"&gt;&lt;font size=\"3\"&gt;&lt;span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"&gt;Liferay Expands to China&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=\"font-style: italic;\"&gt;Company Opens Dalian Office&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br style=\"font-style: italic;\" /&gt;&lt;span style=\"font-style: italic;\"&gt;In Response to Rapid Growth&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"&gt;DALIAN, CHINA &amp;ndash; (October 9, 2007) &lt;/span&gt;&amp;ndash; Liferay, Inc., provider of the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal and content management system, today announced the opening of a new Asian&amp;nbsp; headquarters in Dalian, China. The new office and local staff supports rapid company growth and product demand.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;By tapping into a rich local talent pool, the Dalian office not only serves to support worldwide product development, but also helps to foster a rich technology exchange,&amp;rdquo; said Bryan Cheung, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s CEO. &amp;ldquo;The open source software movement is growing at a phenomenal rate in China. Liferay aims to help foster and expand it.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Located in the Dalian Hi-tech Industrial Zone, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s new office joins many other global IT firms in leveraging access to Dalian&amp;rsquo;s regional technical universities and an IT-savvy workforce. The Industrial Zone was one of the first state-level hi-tech zones approved by the state council and has been home to IT mainstays such as Accenture, HP and IBM for several years. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Establishing a local presence will also give us access to new business opportunities&amp;mdash;not just in China, but in Hong Kong, South Korea and Japan as well,&amp;rdquo; continued Cheung. &amp;ldquo;Our office is headed up by members of our US team who have the requisite experience and knowledge to lead local talent and spearhead business opportunities in the long-term.&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp; Liferay is also leveraging the local business expertise of local technology firm, Auksoft Technology, in the areas of talent selection and staffing.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s flagship open source product, enjoys immense popularity around the world averaging roughly 40,000 downloads per month, more than any other java-based portal in the open source realm. A significant portion of this traffic is from China, where the market has shown impressive adoption of open source software and where an independently formed Liferay User Group already meets on a monthly basis in Beijing. Within enterprises, the product is being chosen for its intuitive UI, architectural flexibility and maturity, strong support for standards, and robust internationalization features. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For more information about Liferay Dalian or Liferay Portal, contact pr@liferay.com or visit www.liferay.com.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients around the world. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles with regional headquarters in Germany and China. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div style=\"text-align: center;\"&gt;# # # #&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;span style=\"font-weight: bold;\"&gt;PRESS CONTACT:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;847/955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20071002095500, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3500, 3501, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3268', 1.0, 'Services-Training-Course_Topics', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[<div class=\"stct-course-header\"><b>Day 1</b></div><div class=\"stct-course-content\"><ul><li>Introduction to Liferay</li><li>Installation <ul><li>Install the Liferay-Tomcat Bundle</li><li>Install Ant &amp; Jikes</li><li>Build the EXT (Extension) Environment</li></ul></li><li>Portlet Fundamentals <ul><li>Overview of JSR 168 (Portlet Specification)</li><li>JSP Portlet</li></ul></li><li>Portlet MVC (Model View Controller) <ul><li>Overview of Struts</li><li>Struts Portlet</li></ul></li></ul></div><div class=\"stct-course-header\"><b>Day 2</b></div><div class=\"stct-course-content\"><ul><li>Configure Liferay to Use a MySQL Database</li><li>Extend the Struts Portlet <ul><li>Overview of the Portlet Lifecycle</li><li>Add the Controller</li></ul></li><li>Install Eclipse <ul><li>Leverage Eclipse to Speed Up Development</li><li>Debug Java Classes Using Eclipse</li></ul></li><li>Create and Retrieve Records from the Database <ul><li>Auto-generate the Service and Persistence Layer</li><li>Implement Business Logic</li><li>Validate Input</li></ul></li><li>Overview of Permissions <ul><li>Integrate Permissions into the Struts Portlet</li></ul></li></ul></div><div class=\"stct-course-header\"><b>Day 3</b></div><div class=\"stct-course-content\"><ul><li>Overview of Spring <ul><li>Overriding Liferay Services</li></ul></li><li>Modular Development <ul><li>JSF Portlet WAR <ul><li>JSF Overview</li><li>Visual JSF Dev Tools</li><li>JSF Portlet</li><li>Migrating JSF Applications to Portlets</li><li>Intro to ICEFaces</li><li>ICEFaces Rich Portlet</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>Extending Liferay <ul><li>Configuring Portal Properties</li><li>Configuring log4j</li><li>Creating a Cookie on Login</li><li>Global Startup Action</li><li>Auditing with Event Management</li><li>Terms of Use Page</li><li>Viewing Cookies within Legacy Webapps</li></ul></li></ul></div><div class=\"stct-course-header\"><b>Day 4</b></div><div class=\"stct-course-content\"><ul><li>Portal Administration</li><li>CMS - How to Build a Website on Top of the Portal <ul><li>Add Articles with the Journal Content Portlet</li></ul></li><li>Create a Theme <ul><li>Configuring Properties</li><li>Editing the Templates</li><li>Editing the CSS</li></ul></li><li>Overview of WSRP</li><li>Web Services in Liferay</li></ul></div>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20071004203500, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3502, 3503, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '2485', 1.0, 'Aboutus-Events-JAX De 2007', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"header\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[W-JAX 2007]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"header-link\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[www.jax.de]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"open-header-link-in-new-window\" type=\"boolean\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[true]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"date\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"type\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"image\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"221951\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1944&amp;t=1207241570153</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"image-link\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[www.jax.de]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"open-image-link-in-new-window\" type=\"boolean\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[true]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"flow\" type=\"list\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[default]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[<p>November 5-9, 2007<br /> Arabella Sheraton Grand Hotel Munchen<br /> Munich, Germany</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>W-JAX is the number one conference for Java, enterprise architecture and SOA. W-JAX offers expert level technical information for project managers, architects and developers. Interactive workshops, in-depth discussion panels, sessions, keynotes and idea exchange form the basis of this annual event.</p> <p>Liferay will be presenting and exhibiting at JAX DE as a Preferred Partner:</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p><strong>Gadgets, Widgets, Web2.0, Social Networking: A developer&rsquo;s perspective</strong> <br /> <em>Jorge Ferrer</em></p> <p>With all the hype around gadgets, widgets, social networks and Web 2.0, it\'s tempting to think that portals have outlived their usefulness as ways to connect people with applications, content, and other people. But enterprises wanting to leverage the benefits of collaborative web applications will find a natural place for them in the portal, which is evolving beyond a simple content aggregator to a complete suite of collaboration and content management tools and a platform for deploying applications. Portals can also take advantage of massive communities like Facebook by bridging the gap between various technologies through the resiliency of the Java platform. We\'ll demonstrate how remotely hosted applications (written in Java, PHP or Ruby) can be quickly deployed over the network.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-ARTICLE', 'BASIC-IMAGE-TEXT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20071009190300, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3504, 3505, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '2481', 1.0, 'Aboutus-Events-OS Meets Business 2008', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"header\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[Open Source Meets Business]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"header-link\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[http://www.heise.de/events/2008/open_source_meets_business/en/]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"open-header-link-in-new-window\" type=\"boolean\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[false]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"date\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"type\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"image\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"394311\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1963&amp;t=1207241358860</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"image-link\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[http://www.heise.de/events/2008/open_source_meets_business/en/]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"open-image-link-in-new-window\" type=\"boolean\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[false]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"flow\" type=\"list\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[default]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[<p>January 22&ndash;24, 2008<br /> Nuremberg Germany</p> <p>Liferay is a partner for this event. A number of our customers will be presenting their portal projects and case studies of their business pain points and Liferay Portal\'s value. CEO, Bryan Cheung will be presenting a <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.heise.de/events/2008/open_source_meets_business/en/keynotes/\">keynote</a> entitled,<b> &quot;Beyond Portals - Collaboration, Social Networking, and Web 2.0 for the Enterprise&quot;</b></p><p>Open Source Meets Business is a congress for CIOs, CTOs, and IT decision makers. As Open Source is gaining importance, the conference analyzes this trend by addressing decision makers from user companies, Open Source projects, as well as from the financial community.</p> <ul>     <li><strong>Deploying Open Source in the Enterprise (Enterprise Summit):</strong> IT managers from companies of all industries and sizes describe their experience in OS software deployment in mission-critical applications.</li>     <li><strong>Open Source projects and their business perspectives (Technology Summit)</strong>: Internationally renowned heads of the Open Source marketplace introduce status and roadmaps of the most important projects and discuss their visions of the future.</li>     <li><strong>Open Source meets Money (Investment Summit)</strong>: Forward-looking investors reveal how they act in the Open Source marketplace. Interesting start ups and companies on a growth path present their concepts and ideas.</li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-ARTICLE', 'BASIC-IMAGE-TEXT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20071009191600, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
