port&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://wiki.liferay.com/index.php/Community_Roles\"&gt;Community-Scoped Roles&lt;/a&gt; (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://wiki.liferay.com/index.php/Dynamic_Management_of_Companies\"&gt;Multiple Enterprise Management, aka Dynamic Company Management&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;ICEfaces Integration for AJAX + JSF&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Deprecate EJB services in favor of Spring POJO\'s&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Tag / Folksonomy and Asset Management Framework (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Expose REST-style JSON Web Services&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Javascript Client Libraries for JSON Web Services&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LAR Import / Export for Themes (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;PHP and Ruby Support&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Security&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Enterprise Password Policy Management w / Provisioning to LDAP (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Active Directory Single-SignOn via NTLM&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://wiki.liferay.com/index.php/Using_OpenID_with_Liferay\"&gt;OpenID Enabled SSO&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Performance improvements&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Database tuning&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Scalability - optimize memory usage&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Integration&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Microsoft Exchange &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;iCal Support - Import\\Export from Calendar Portlet&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Yahoo Maps&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Full WebDAV Support&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Context-Sensitive Help&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Liferay Eclipse&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Portlet Development&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Portlet Deployment&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Portlets&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Tags Admin (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Tags Content (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Tagify Existing Portlets (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;PHP and Ruby Sample Portlets&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Sample ICEfaces Portlet&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Themes/Layout&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Role-base Theme Management (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Standardize on jQuery JavaScript Framework&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Simplify Theme Development Process&amp;nbsp; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Semantic and Non-Obtrusive Markup&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Standards Compliance&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Free-form (WebOS) Layout&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://wiki.liferay.com/index.php/Page_link_to_another_page\"&gt;Link to Layout Type&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://wiki.liferay.com/index.php/WAP_Mobile_Device_Themes_with_Liferay\"&gt;Mobile Device Support&lt;/a&gt; (Sponsored Feature)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070803000700, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3590, 3591, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '2315', 1.0, 'Community-Road_Map-Release_Process', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root>\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content>&lt;div class=\"release-process-container\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;We plan to release new versions of Liferay at 3-4 month intervals -- roughly 3-4 releases every year. Our philosophy has always been to release early and often.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;During our development cycle for a particular release, we are always forward-looking at the following two releases down the road. Every release is different. We may plan to focus on new functionality in one release, usability and performance on another, or purely on backend features and developer tools. Mostly likely there will be advancements at some level on all fronts.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Although our intention is to release every three to four months, exact dates need to be set on a release by release basis. Depending on community and customer-driven features and contributions, these dates are subject to change.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The following describes our release schedule:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Early Access Releases (i.e. liferay-portal-a.b-EAn)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;When the development team reaches certain milestones, we may decide to make a number of early access (EA) releases. The intention for these releases is to allow the Liferay commnunity to test drive key new functionality and have an opportunity to provide valuable feedback before the features are finalized. We will provide minimal packaging for the EA releases -- Tomcat bundle and source code.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Feature Freeze&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;No new functionality will be introduced after this point. Only bug fixes are allowed to be committed to SVN. At this time a branch is made off SVN trunk for the new release. This is the branch where all releases related to this particular version are made (Release Candidates, Generally Available, Maintenance). For example, if we are planning to release version a.b, we will create a branch named /branches/a.b.x in SVN.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Stabilization and Release Candidates (i.e. liferay-portal-a.b-RCn)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;During this time period we will be working to stablize the upcoming release. When a substantial number of issues have been addressed and gone through our QA process, we will make a release candidate available. During this phase a number of release candidates will be made, and when all serious issues have been addressed, the final release -- Generally Available (GA) release will be made. We will provide full packaging for RC releases (app servers, themes, portlets, etc).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Generally Available Release (i.e. liferay-portal-a.b-GA)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;The final, publicly available, fully packaged, officially supported release.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Maintenance Releases (i.e liferay-portal-a.b.c-GA)&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;A bug fix release. Any bugs found after the final release will be addressed by any number of maintenance releases. We will be implementing process this following our 4.3 release.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070803003300, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
