in 2005, HanseMerkur\'s investment portfolio registered at around 3 billion EUR in 2005.</p> <h2>Challenge</h2> <p>HanseMerkur set a goal to dramatically improve its Web presence and to increase the amount of information available online to prospective customers. The company envisioned a site populated with marketing content in mixed formats like HTML, graphics and PDF. Visitors to the site would interact with online content including contracts, job applications and downloadable forms. Hence, a content management system (CMS) capable of managing its 350+ pages of content was high on the list of desired capabilities and features.</p> <h2>Resolution</h2> <p>After evaluating a number of solutions, HanseMerkur decided an open source portal would work best as a service-oriented architecture (SOA) framework. HanseMerkur then quickly chose Liferay Portal as the best candidate to provide a foundation for this enterprise-wide SOA. Liferay&rsquo;s ease of use, scalable CMS and high degree of functionality compared to that of the other portal offerings further solidified the company\'s decision.</p> <p>Moreover, HanseMerkur was impressed with the Liferay consulting team&rsquo;s vision and depth of knowledge. HanseMerkur traveled to the CeBIT conference specifically to meet with Liferay representatives, after which a proof of concept was delivered. As Liferay provided further ideas and vision for the portal&rsquo;s potential, this initial effort grew into a full collaborative development and integration engagement leveraging personnel from HanseMerkur and Liferay&rsquo;s German and U.S. organizations.</p> <p>Despite a detailed yet oft-changing list of specifications, the HanseMerkur site was successfully delivered under tight deadlines. The end result was a portal that exceeded the client&rsquo;s original vision and showcases the fruits of its collaboration with Liferay. Besides the strong, scalable content management capabilities demanded, the portal also delivers added site functionality and enhanced marketing potential through a Search Engine Optimization (SEO) feature that HanseMerkur sponsored and which was immediately added to Liferay\'s 4.2 release.</p> <p>Liferay Portal will continue to provide a framework for further enterprise integration throughout the HanseMerkur organization. Following the first successful team effort and the establishment of a strong working relationship, Liferay is currently working with HanseMerkur on new development and enhancements. Innovations leveraging Liferay Portal to streamline HanseMerkur&rsquo;s back-end processes and thereby bolster the company&rsquo;s competitive edge in the insurance marketplace are among the key projects in progress.</p> <ul> <li><strong>Scalability </strong>&ndash; Liferay Portal&rsquo;s CMS easily manages HanseMerkur&rsquo;s 350+ pages of mixed content. Liferay Portal enables HanseMerkur to add hardware incrementally to comfortably scale the site in complexity and size.</li> <li><strong>Enhanced marketing potential </strong>&ndash; Search Engine Optimization (SEO) now enables the site to automatically and dynamically optimize its visibility on leading Web search engines, keeping the HanseMerkur brand at the forefront of consumer minds.</li> <li><strong>Improved site functionality</strong> &ndash; The portal acts as an aggregator of services and allows the end-user to complete an insurance policy via the website.</li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image1\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1592\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1592&amp;t=1201073653533</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image2\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1594\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1594&amp;t=1201073653535</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image3\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1596\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1596&amp;t=1201073653538</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image4\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1598\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1598&amp;t=1201073653541</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image5\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image6\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image7\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image8\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image9\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image1\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1593\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1584&amp;t=1201073653581</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image2\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1595\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1585&amp;t=1201073653584</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image3\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1597\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1586&amp;t=1201073653587</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image4\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1599\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1587&amp;t=1201073653591</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image5\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image6\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image7\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image8\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-elemen