ay design patterns.</p><h2>Latest&nbsp;Release</h2><p>Come and learn about the&nbsp;latest&nbsp;features&nbsp;in&nbsp;Liferay Portal 4.4!</p><h2>Hands-On Training</h2><p>You\'ll get&nbsp;the experience you need, so that you\'ll be ready to develop portlets on your own&nbsp;by the end of the course.</p><h2>Subject Matter Experts</h2><p>The course will be led by the Liferay experts who designed the software.</p><h2>Development Environment</h2><p>Although Liferay runs on almost any server and database, we will&nbsp;be using&nbsp;Tomcat, MySQL and Eclipse because this is the fastest&nbsp;setup&nbsp;for development. We may also touch upon installation with other application servers and databases as well.</p><h2>Prerequisites</h2><p>Basic knowledge of Java and Servlets is required.</p><p>A&nbsp;laptop with Windows XP and a wireless card is required.<br />- Recommended system requirements: 2.0Ghz Core Duo, 2GB RAM</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-CONTENT-SIDEBAR', 'BASIC-CONTENT-SIDEBAR', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070803175300, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
