95847a8f5723cfca6b3fd9946506\\static\\inactive_r.compat.gif)\"></skype:span></skype:span> <o:p></o:p></font></font></o:p></p>\n<p class=\"MsoPlainText\" style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 0pt\"><font size=\"2\"><font face=\"Tahoma\">Fax: +49 (0)6105 966-100<o:p></o:p></font></font></p>\n<p>Ask for Liferay Rates when&nbsp;making reservations.&nbsp;A&nbsp;airport schuttle bus service is available.&nbsp;</p>--><p><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.frankfurt.radissonsas.com/\">Radisson SAS Hotel, Frankfurt</a><br /><font size=\"-1\">Franklinstr. 65, Frankfurt/Main<br />069 770155-0<br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://maps.google.de/maps?ie=UTF8&amp;oe=utf-8&amp;client=firefox-a&amp;q=radisson+hotels&amp;near=Frankfurt+am+Main&amp;fb=1&amp;cid=0,0,13924465622800749477&amp;z=16&amp;iwloc=A\">Location Map</a><br type=\"_moz\" /></font></p><h2>Additional Information</h2><p>Please note that a laptop is required for this course.</p><h2>How to Register</h2><p>Email <a href=\"mailto:sales@liferay.com\">sales@liferay.com</a> to register.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n		<dynamic-content language-id=\"de_DE\"><![CDATA[<h2>Training Schedule</h2> <p><a href=\"@root_path@/web/guest/services/training/frankfurt/course_topics\">Course Topics</a></p> <h2>Training Time</h2> <p>October 16 - 19, 2007<br /> 9am-5pm daily</p> <h2>Course Details</h2> <p>4 days Developer Training<br /> &euro;3200</p> <h2>Location</h2> <p>Liferay GmbH<br /> Robert-Bosch-Str. 11<br /> 63225 Langen</p><h2>Additional Information</h2> <p>Please note that a laptop is required for this course.</p> <h2>How to Register</h2> <p>Email <a href=\"mailto:sales@liferay.com\">sales@liferay.com</a> to register.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"main-content\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[<h2>Overview</h2><p>Liferay will host a public training seminar in Frankfurt, Germany. Core topics include&nbsp;portlet development, customizing the portal with the extension environment, content management and themes.</p><p>By the end of the course you will know&nbsp;how to create portlets using Liferay best practices,&nbsp;auto-generate the service and persistence layer and debug effectively&nbsp;by&nbsp;understanding Liferay design patterns.</p><h2>Latest&nbsp;Release</h2><p>Come and learn about the&nbsp;latest&nbsp;features&nbsp;in&nbsp;Liferay Portal 4.4 and upcoming version Liferay 5.0</p><h2>Hands-On Training</h2><p>You\'ll get&nbsp;the experience you need, so that you\'ll be ready to develop portlets on your own&nbsp;by the end of the course.</p><h2>Subject Matter Experts</h2><p>The course will be led by the Liferay experts who designed the software.</p><h2>Development Environment</h2><p>Although Liferay runs on almost any server and database, we will&nbsp;be using&nbsp;Tomcat, MySQL and Eclipse because this is the fastest&nbsp;setup&nbsp;for development. We may also touch upon installation with other application servers and databases as well.</p><h2>Prerequisites</h2><p>Basic knowledge of Java and Servlets is required.</p><p>A&nbsp;laptop with Windows XP and a wireless card is required.<br />- Recommended system requirements: 2.0Ghz Core Duo, 2GB RAM</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n		<dynamic-content language-id=\"de_DE\"><![CDATA[<h2>Overview</h2> <p>Liferay will host a public training seminar October 16 - 19, 2007 in Langen near Frankfurt, Germany. The seminar will be comprehensive, covering architecture, installation, portlet development, themes, and CMS.</p><p>This course is designed to help you come up to speed on the functionality and development of Liferay Portal.&nbsp; It will help you to increase your productivity as well as introduce you to valuable new features.</p><h2>NEW 4.3 Release</h2> <p>Come and learn about the new features Liferay Portal 4.3 has to offer!</p> <h2>Hands-On Training</h2> <p>We will take you through the entire process of portlet development and teach you industry best practices.</p> <h2>Subject Matter Experts</h2> <p>The course will be led by the Liferay experts who designed the software.</p> <h2>Development Environment</h2> <p>For development we will setup Tomcat on Eclipse and use MySQL for the database. Although Liferay can be used with any application server and database, the above setup is the fastest in terms of development. We may also touch upon installation with other application servers and databases as well.</p> <h2>Prerequisites</h2> <p>Basic knowledge of Java and Servlets is required. The course will be intensive, but we will make sure to answer any questions you have to ensure that you have a solid grasp of the technology by the end of the course.</p> <p>Please note that a laptop is required for this course.</p> <ul> <li>Operating System: Windows XP</li><li>Minimum System Requirements: 1.4 GHz 512MB RAM</li> <li>Recommended System Requirements: 2.0 GHz 1GB RAM</li> <li>Wireless Card Required</li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <h2>Contact Us</h2> <p>Email us at <a href=\"mailto:sales@liferay.com\">sales@liferay.com</a> to register or if you have any questions.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-CONTENT-SIDEBAR', 'BASIC-CONTENT-SIDEBAR', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070726173400, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
