insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3889, 3890, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '2815', 1.0, 'Stories-L\'Anella', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n	<dynamic-element name=\"company-image\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1749\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1685&amp;t=1201072523153</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"company-link\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[http://www.anella.cat]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"company-link-name\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[www.anella.cat]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"quote\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[<p><font size=\"3\"><em>&ldquo;Thanks to Liferay, COPCA developed a first class technological platform while minimizing costs. Because Liferay is an open source solution, we are able to quickly respond to business requirements, easily developing small customizations over standard components. Two years after choosing Liferay Portal, we can still say we made the right selection and continue to work with this platform.&rdquo; </em></font></p><p align=\"right\">--José Oliver, COPCA&rsquo;s Digitalization Manager.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[<h2>Company Profile</h2> <p>The Consortium for the Commercial Promotion of Catalonia (COPCA), in affiliation with the Ministry of Innovation, University and Enterprise, is the Catalan government&rsquo;s tool to promote the internationalization of Catalan companies and their adaptation to the new guidelines of the global economy.</p> <p>COPCA comprises the Government of Catalonia, the Catalan Chambers of Commerce and Industry and the main sector and export associations, along with entities related to the world of trade, finance and overseas trade training. In total there are almost a hundred members.</p> <p>As a service centre for the internalization of Catalan companies, COPCA has a team of experts specialized in export start-up, market assessment and international consolidation of companies. They are located in Catalonia as well as in COPCA&rsquo;s international network of Business Promotion Centers, spread over 31 countries.</p> <h2>Challenge</h2> <p>COPCA wanted to build a virtual space where Catalan enterprises could share experiences, knowledge and support from both government and other organizations. Because COPCA&rsquo;s offices are spread worldwide, it was necessary to build a collaborative platform that would be accessible by employees in any location, allowing them to share information, resources and applications.</p> <p>The original technologies used to do this at COPCA varied by region so an upgrade also served as an opportunity for organizational homogenization.</p> <h2>Resolution</h2><p>&nbsp;</p> <p>After assessing a number of technology solutions, both open source and commercial, based on COPCA&rsquo;s functional, technological, and economic requirements, the decision was made to use Liferay Portal. The new virtual space, called l&rsquo;Anella, (www.anella.cat) is the new virtual space that powers Catalonia&rsquo;s internalization. Today, Liferay is at the core of COPCA&rsquo;s virtual desktop.</p> <p>L\'Anella\'s aim is to service professionals of all areas: business organizations, associations, agencies and institutions. Essentially, it is a tool for communications, knowledge sharing, and business process management for customers and employees, providing:</p><ul> <li>Integrated user management system. Centralized user, roles, communities, and privileges management using an LDAP</li> <li>Community management and collaborative tools</li> <li>Application, information, and service aggregation</li> <li>Business Process Management</li> <li>Communication and knowledge sharing tool</li> <li>On-line electronic transactions</li> <li>Document Management System</li> </ul> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>In close collaboration with COPCA, the project was implemented by <a href=\"http://www.isoco.com/\">iSOCO</a>, a technological consultancy in charge of the platform development, installation and personalization.</p> <p>The resulting platform is currently being used by COPCA&rsquo;s employees and more than 10.000 registered users from various Catalan companies. New services and applications are added to the system each month to resolve new requirements as needed by the community.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image1\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image1\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image2\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image2\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image3\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image3\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image4\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image4\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image5\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image5\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image6\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image6\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image7\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image7\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image8\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image8\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image9\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image9\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'SHOWCASE', 'SHOWCASE', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070801204700, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3891, 3892, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '2823', 1.0, 'Stories-FNFP', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n	<dynamic-element name=\"company-image\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1884\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1779&amp;t=1201073119927</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"company-link\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[http://www.fnfp.org]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"company-link-name\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[www.fnfp.org]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"quote\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\"><![CDATA[<p><font size=\"3\"><em>&quot;Liferay Portal allows us to provide a sense of community and involvement that is crucial to the coordination of activities and dialogue between geographically dispersed users.&rdquo;</em></font></p><p><font size=\"3\"><em> </em></font></p> <p align=\"right\">―Mawae Morton, Director, First Nations Futures Program</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[<h2>Company Profile</h2> <p>Kamehameha Schools is a nonprofit institution dedicated to educating children of Hawaiian ancestry. Towards this goal, Kamehameha Schools is working in partnership with other indigenous communities that hold land trusts from Alaska and New Zealand to create a fellowship program for leadership development in natural resource management.</p> <p>The fellowship program, First Nations Futures Program (FNFP), partners with a consortium of academic institutions. In collaboration with indigenous community leaders and environmental experts, Stanford University faculty host, teach and facilitate an annual Leadership Institute for fellows.</p> <h2>Challenge</h2> <p>Kamehameha Schools was challenged to bring together several geographically dispersed communities. A key objective was to provide collaborative tools that would enable and encourage communication among the participants in Alaska, Hawaii and New Zealand.</p> <p>The portal needed to fulfill a marketing role and publicize the fellowship program to participating communities, partners, donors and the general public.</p> <h2>Resolution</h2> <p>Wired Moon, the consulting company working in collaboration with Kamehameha Schools, was tasked with selecting an appropriate tool to serve the unique needs of the fellowship program.</p> <p>After reviewing several portal products Liferay Portal was selected for its superior out-of-the-box functionality, ease of use and low cost of ownership. Liferay Portal compliance with JSR standards also allowed easy integration with other portal tools (outside of Liferay), as well as simple customization on top of the portal. This granted the organization great flexibility in building a sustainable solution that could be customized in the long-term for its specific and changing needs. Meanwhile, the ability to easily customize the look and feel of the external website addressed marketing and branding issues with a minimal investment of time.</p> <p>However, the real benefit of Liferay Portal for the fellowship program was its ability to facilitate a sense of community. The organization depended heavily on the Document Library, Image Gallery and built-in content management system to provide a common space for sharing. Out of the box portlets, such as the Calendar and Message Boards, facilitated communication within the community.</p> <p>Wired Moon enhanced the portal with a streaming video portlet for displaying key videos within internal and external portions of the site. Wired Moon also integrated 123FlashChat into the portal to provide a more interactive and integrated chat experience for users.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image1\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1885\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1885&amp;t=1201073119938</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image1\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1886\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1780&amp;t=1201073119940</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image2\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1887\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1887&amp;t=1201073119941</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image2\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1888\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1781&amp;t=1201073119944</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image3\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1889\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1889&amp;t=1201073119946</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image3\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1890\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1782&amp;t=1201073119948</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image4\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1891\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1891&amp;t=1201073119951</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image4\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1892\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1783&amp;t=1201073119953</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"full-image5\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1893\">/image/journal/article?img_id=1893&amp;t=1201073119956</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"thumb-image5\" type=\"image\">\n		<dynamic-content id=\"1894\">/image/journal/article?img