t; &lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt; &lt;td valign=\"bottom\" align=\"left\" colspan=\"3\"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt; &lt;td valign=\"bottom\" align=\"left\" colspan=\"3\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt; &lt;td valign=\"bottom\" align=\"left\" colspan=\"3\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt; &lt;/tr&gt;&lt;tr&gt; &lt;td valign=\"top\" align=\"left\" colspan=\"3\"&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://www.mongolbank.mn/web/guest/home\" target=\"_blank\"&gt;Bank of Mongolia&lt;/a&gt; (Mongolia)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://www.employersdirect.com/web/guest/home\" target=\"_blank\"&gt;Employers Direct Insurance Company&lt;/a&gt; (US)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Fortune 100 provider of investment products (US)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://www.hansemerkur.de/\" target=\"_blank\"&gt;HanseMerkur &lt;/a&gt;- (Germany) &lt;a href=\"../../../../../web/guest/stories/hansemerkur\"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=\"http://www.healthmarkets.com/\" target=\"_blank\"&gt;Health Markets&lt;/a&gt; - (US) &lt;a href=\"../../../../../web/guest/stories/healthmarkets\"&gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt;Story&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leading online trading company (US)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Leading online banking solutions provider (US)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Noridian (US)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Sparkasse KolnBonn (Germany)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Top 10 European Investment Bank (Germany)&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/td&gt; &lt;td valign=\"top\" align=\"left\" colspan=\"3\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt; &lt;td valign=\"top\" align=\"left\" colspan=\"3\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/td&gt; &lt;/tr&gt; &lt;/tbody&gt; &lt;/table&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20071119201800, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3994, 3995, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '2997', 1.0, 'PR-Liferay 3.6.1', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;font size=\"4\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Unveils Liferay Portal 3.6, Adding More New Features&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font size=\"4\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To Industry&amp;rsquo;s Most Versatile Portal Development Tool&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;New Version of Software Includes Better Content Management, New Interface Features;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Solution Offers More Out-of-Box Functionality/Integration Than Other Open-Source Products&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES, CA&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; Liferay, a leading provider of enterprise-class open source software products and solutions, has announced the release of Liferay Portal Version 3.6, the latest version of its flagship web portal development platform. Its new convenience and productivity features, headlined by new drag-anddrop portlets and a new hot-deployable theme capability, provide even more power and flexibility to what is already the most complete, versatile open-source portal development tool on the market today.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is unparalleled in its feature sets, integration capability, and out-of-the-box functionality. Offering the most portlet options of any open source portal, Liferay Portal has bundled collaboration tools that include email, blogs, calendar, document library, journal (CMS), image gallery, message boards, weather, stocks, polls, RSS, Wiki and more.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s ability to integrate with any middleware stack or database including JBoss JEMS, BEA Platform, WebSphere, Oracle and others, makes Liferay Portal totally application server and database agnostic. Its open-source architecture, built in J2EE, completely conforms with the industry standard JSR-168 portal API; what&amp;rsquo;s more, Liferay Portal is offered under a no-cost MIT license that allows organizations to use, modify, or distribute Liferay freely.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay is committed to offering enterprises a portal development solution that simplifies deployment tasks for developers while empowering administrators and users alike,&amp;rdquo; said Brian Chan, founder and chief software architect of Liferay. &amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal 3.6 not only gives companies important new capabilities that benefit the enterprise, but also makes life easier and more productive for employees and other users.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Versatile, Powerful&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal Version 3.6 focuses on improving content navigation, presentation, and&lt;br /&gt;effectiveness. Specific upgrades and new features include:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hot-Deployable Themes&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;the ability to change a portal&amp;rsquo;s look-and-feel on the fly without restarting the server (application server must support hot-deploy);&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drag-and-Drop Portlets&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;eliminates the need to use up/down arrows to move a portlet on a page. Simply click on the portlet and move it anywhere using the mouse;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Portlet Instancing&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;a feature that creates multiple &amp;ldquo;instances&amp;rdquo; of the same portlet for users who need multiples of the same application. Can be used, for example, to create real-time stock tickers for more than one company or multiple radar weather maps for various cities;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New &amp;ldquo;Runtime-Portlet&amp;rdquo; Tag&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;enables portlet instances to be placed inside Content Management System (CMS) templates or articles, e.g. for log-in or other real-time functions;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Portlet Aggregator&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;supports the creation of portlet layouts according to customized or predesigned templates for easier page organization;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nested/Child Pages&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;allows a page (child) to be &amp;ldquo;nested&amp;rdquo; inside a main (&amp;ldquo;parent&amp;rdquo;) page for hierarchical content organization;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Navigation Portlet&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;automatically creates a navigation menu for a given portal page or series of pages.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition, Liferay Portal 3.6 includes a breadcrumb portlet feature, a Journal Content Portlet for displaying a CMS article on a page, better CMS, and support for JavaServer Faces. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Version 3.6 is available in both current editions of Liferay Portal&amp;mdash;Liferay Portal Professional, the standard product; and Liferay Portal Enterprise, which includes all Professional features plus the ability to cluster portlet transactions across multiple servers. The product is available for immediate download in both editions.&lt;br /&gt;To download either product, or for more information about Liferay and Liferay Portal 3.6, go to www.liferay.com.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;font size=\"1\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=\"1\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay is a leading provider of high-value, open source software products that help firms optimize their business, increase productivity, and differentiate themselves from the competition. The company&amp;rsquo;s flagship product, Liferay Portal, is an enterprise-class portal development tool designed to handle the most demanding applications while ensuring scalability and robust performance for firms across all industries. Liferay monetizes its business by offering expert support for its no-cost products; its corporate philosophy emphasizes making a difference in the world by supporting respected non-profit organizations such as Samaritan&amp;rsquo;s Purse and World Vision through regular financial support. The privately-held company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information about Liferay, please visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;font size=\"1\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;# # # #&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731203100, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3996, 3997, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3001', 1.0, 'PR-Walden Media', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;Chronicles of Narnia&amp;rdquo; Producers Gives Liferay&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Leading Role In Its Public, Community Web Sites&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;em&gt;Web Portal Technology Speeds Development of Walden Media&amp;rsquo;s Collaboration Tools&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;em&gt;For Parents and Educators; Company Says Needs are Met at &amp;ldquo;Fraction of the Cost&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES, CA &amp;ndash; February 28, 2006 &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; Liferay, a leading provider of enterprise-class open source software products and solutions, today announced that Walden Media, the Hollywood production company responsible for hit movies such as &amp;ldquo;Holes&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, The Witch and the Wardrobe,&amp;rdquo; has chosen Liferay&amp;rsquo;s web portal technology to power both its public web site as well as its online portal for educators. Using Liferay Portal, Walden Media is able to support an international online community interested in using the company&amp;rsquo;s films to inspire children to read and learn.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Walden Media was founded with the mission &amp;ldquo;to make movies that are inherently educational.&amp;rdquo;The four-year old company quickly made a name for itself with films such as &amp;ldquo;Holes&amp;rdquo; and &amp;ldquo;Because of Winn Dixie&amp;rdquo; before hitting the big time with its blockbuster, &amp;ldquo;The Chronicles of Narnia: The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe,&amp;rdquo; produced in association with The Walt Disney Company.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Key to Walden Media&amp;rsquo;s strategy is its close relationships with schools and the literary community. Teachers, librarians and authors are all consulted on the source material that drives most projects; the same partners are then provided with a wealth of curriculum and resources built around the theatrical release. In everything it does, Walden Media is consumed with helping young adults develop a lifelong interest in learning.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; To that end, Walden Media wanted to expand its already burgeoning web presence serving teachers, administrators, parents and youth leaders. Its requirements were fourfold: one, to offer these users a broad set of personalized collaboration tools so they could share ideas and strategies with each other; two, to integrate these tools within an attractive, Flash-integrated public web site; three, to make it easy for non-technical content authors and editors to maintain the site; and four, to create a single web interface that would allow users both inside and outside the company to use enterprise applications.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Liferay Portal was the development tool Walden Media chose for its ambitious Internet needs. &amp;ldquo;Liferay&amp;rsquo;s sound architecture and standards compliance truly make it shine as a platform for both application and content aggregation,&amp;rdquo; said Daniel Kim, Director of Web Development for Walden Media. &amp;ldquo;It was the only solution we evaluated that met all of our business and service-level requirements, and it did so at a small fraction of the cost of commercial alternatives.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Liferay Portal exceeds at enabling enterprises to easily aggregate disparate applications into a single, easy-to-use and attractive web interface. Its array of out-of-the-box portlets enabled Walden Media to immediately offer its members tools to facilitate information exchange, increase productivity, and simplify information access.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &amp;ldquo;Walden Media wanted to make it easy for content managers to add, edit and manage the site easily, which is what Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s Content Management System is designed to do,&amp;rdquo; noted Brian Chan, founder and chief software architect at Liferay. &amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal lets these people save text as templates using XML file extracts. They also can easily track versions and approvals as they go using Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s workflow features.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Walden Media&amp;rsquo;s newly-enhanced web site is rich in user features. In addition to showcasing new and upcoming films using Flash multimedia technology, the site provides curriculums for download as well as interactive applets for creating customized classroom worksheets, book plates, certificates and stickers. By completing a free registration, users can also access the community area where they can post questions and suggestions about leveraging Walden Media titles in schools and libraries.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Liferay Portal has become a critical component of Walden Media&amp;rsquo;s Service Oriented Architecture strategy. With the success of Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s various portal tools, the studio continues to leverage the new platform as a means of providing role-based&amp;nbsp; application access for its user community.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For more information about the Liferay Portal open source portal development tool, including how to download the software, visit www.Liferay.com.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay is a leading provider of high-value, open source software products that help firms optimize their business, increase productivity, and differentiate themselves from the competition. The company&amp;rsquo;s flagship product, Liferay Portal, is an enterprise-class portal development tool designed to handle the most demanding applications while ensuring scalability and robust performance for firms across all industries. Liferay monetizes its business by offering expert support, training, and professional services for its no-cost products; its corporate philosophy emphasizes making a difference in the world by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;supporting respected non-profit organizations such as Samaritan&amp;rsquo;s Purse and World Vision through regular financial support. The privately-held company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information about Liferay, please visit www.Liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;# # # #&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731203500, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (3998, 3999, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3005', 1.0, 'PR-Goodwill Launch', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Goodwill Industries Relies On Liferay Portal To&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bring 80,000 Worldwide Workers Together&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Portal Development Technology Also Drives Nonprofit&amp;rsquo;s Main Website&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES, CA &lt;/strong&gt;-- Liferay, a leading provider of enterprise-class open source software products and solutions, has announced that its Liferay Portal web portal development technology is the key software driving MyGoodwill, a new organizational Intranet site for employees and volunteers of Goodwill Industries International. MyGoodwill, which began operation this week, is a landmark organizational tool for the international nonprofit, enabling thousands of Goodwill staff worldwide to collaborate, share best practices and engage in real-time learning.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Goodwill Industries International, based in Rockville, Maryland, provides job training and career programs for people with disabilities, welfare recipients, low-wage workers and other job seekers. Last year more than 723,000 people benefited from Goodwill&amp;rsquo;s career services The organization, which also fulfills commercial services for government and private industry, operates 2,015 retail stores and an Internet auction site, www.shopgoodwill.com, to build revenue for its programs.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The goal of MyGoodwill is to connect Goodwill staffers around the world in order to enhance the organization&amp;rsquo;s services and share best practices between the different local Goodwill agencies. In addition to collaborative chat and message board capabilities, the new portal distributes knowledge efficiently via blogs, a document repository and, eventually, &amp;ldquo;Wiki&amp;rdquo; pages that will be updated on a regular basis by visitors. MyGoodwill also furnishes a growing collection of Computer-Based Training&lt;br /&gt;modules, or CBTs, that allow staffers to take online courses.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The portal was designed to accommodate as many as 100,000 people in the future. Liferay Portal, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s flagship product, is also the key technology framework behind Goodwill&amp;rsquo;s public web site, www.goodwill.org, which was re-introduced during the summer. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal is an open source product that provides Goodwill a number of business and operational advantages,&amp;rdquo; said Steve Bergman, Chief Information Officer of Goodwill Industries International. &amp;ldquo;First and foremost is an accelerated return on investment, which allows us to make additional site features possible sooner. Liferay Portal is easily adaptable to Goodwill&amp;rsquo;s data center architecture and the diverse combination of technologies that we employ. Finally, it offers exceptional robustness and scalability. Liferay Portal was by far the most cost effective and efficient portal technology we considered.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is one of the most reliable and flexible portal development tools on the market today. Its J2EE architecture, which conforms with the JSR-168 portal API standard, allows users to easily integrate with any of the wide array of JSR-168 portlets marketed by third-party vendors. It also dependably interfaces with virtually any database or middleware stack including JBoss JEMS, BEA Platform, WebSphere, and Oracle.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal offers an amazing range of capabilities, typically enabling out-of-the-box portal development,&amp;rdquo; said Brian Chan, founder and chief software architect of Liferay. &amp;ldquo;And because Liferay Portal is marketed under a no-cost, open-source MIT license, users can easily modify the application or access the Liferay user community for additional capabilities as needed.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In Goodwill&amp;rsquo;s case, Liferay Portal supported roughly 70% of the organization&amp;rsquo;s desired MyGoodwill functionality out of the box. &amp;ldquo;I was happily surprised at Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s easy integration with portlets from outside providers,&amp;rdquo; Bergman stated. &amp;ldquo;This kind of flexibility has allowed us to move our Intranet presence to a state-of-the-art portal offering in minimal time.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To learn more about Liferay and Liferay Portal, visit www.Liferay.com.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay is a leading provider of high-value, open source software products that help firms optimize their business, increase productivity, and differentiate themselves from the competition. The company&amp;rsquo;s flagship product, Liferay Portal, is an enterprise-class portal development tool designed to handle the most demanding applications while ensuring scalability and robust performance for firms across all industries. Liferay monetizes its business by offering expert support for its no-cost products; its corporate philosophy emphasizes making a difference in the world by supporting respected non-profit organizations such as Samaritan&amp;rsquo;s Purse and World Vision through regular financial support. The privately-held company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information about Liferay, please visit www.Liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;# # # #&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731203800, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4000, 4001, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3009', 1.0, 'PR-Themes', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay &amp;ldquo;Portal Themes&amp;rdquo; Contest Attracts Diverse Entries,&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demonstrates Power Of Open Source Approach&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Unique Competition Expands Collection of Free GUI Themes Available&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;To Liferay Portal Users; Prizes Include Monies Donated to Winners&amp;rsquo; Favorite Charities&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES, CA &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; Liferay, a leading provider of enterprise-class open source software products and solutions, has announced its recent &amp;ldquo;portal themes&amp;rdquo; contest was a huge success, attracting quality entries from around the world and underscoring the vitality of the company&amp;rsquo;s open source approach which stimulates volunteerism for the common good. Results of the contest, which was initiated to build the library of graphic user interface &amp;ldquo;skins&amp;rdquo; available to the company&amp;rsquo;s free Liferay Portal web portal development platform, can be seen at www.liferay.com/web/guest/downloads/themes.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition to prizes that included Apple iPods, winners in Liferay&amp;rsquo;s contest were given cash gifts of up to $500 to be donated to their charity of choice. The charitable contribution aspect of the contest was in keeping with the corporate vision of Liferay, which places a high emphasis on global philanthropy. A significant portion of Liferay&amp;rsquo;s corporate profits are given each month to respected non-profit organizations such as WorldVision and Samaritan&amp;rsquo;s Purse; most recently the company contributed to humanitarian efforts addressing Hurricane Katrina, the African AIDS crisis and the Pakistan earthquake.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Our company is continually impressed by the excellence and dedication demonstrated in the contributions of individuals who in the spirit of volunteerism give their time and talent to Liferay &amp;ndash; that&amp;rsquo;s what open source is all about,&amp;rdquo; said Bryan Cheung, partner and principal consultant at Liferay. &amp;ldquo;These folks look beyond themselves to help others, submitting enhancements and fixes that will benefit our entire user community. And the themes contest shows that they have a lot of fun doing it. Of course they love the challenge of the work itself, but it&amp;rsquo;s also nice to know that what you do is going to make life easier for thousands of people. That&amp;rsquo;s what&amp;rsquo;s great about getting involved with a product that has as much momentum and support as Liferay does. We sincerely thank everyone who participated in our themes contest and encourage our user community to make use of the winning entries.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is an advanced web portal development platform that is both powerful and easy to use. Featuring drag-and-drop portlets and hot-deployable themes, the application comes standard with more portlet options than any other open source alternative, enabling users to quickly deploy rich web portal applications that incorporate content management, collaboration tools, WSRP services, and basics such as email, address books, blogs, calendars, weather, news, stocks and much more.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;A healthy user community and active development and support team behind Liferay Portal ensure that custom integration into existing business applications and processes can be accomplished quickly and at very low cost. The free software can run either as a J2EE application or in a standalone servlet container; moreover, Liferay Portal supports limitless clustering for scalability and conforms to the industry standard JSR-168 portal API, ensuring inter-portlet compatibility.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Finally, Liferay Portal has been successfully tested for compatibility with an extremely broad array of application servers and databases, virtually guaranteeing compatibility with existing applications. Entries in Liferay&amp;rsquo;s themes contest were judged by Liferay staff for their aesthetic quality, ease of use, originality, and programming elegance. The three-month competition ended October 31, 2005, with winners announced in early November.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay is a leading provider of high-value, open source software products that help firms optimize their &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;business, increase productivity, and differentiate themselves from the competition. The company&amp;rsquo;s &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;flagship product, Liferay Portal, is an enterprise-class portal development tool designed to handle the &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;most demanding applications while ensuring scalability and robust performance for firms across all &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;industries. Liferay monetizes its business by offering expert support, training, and professional services &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;for its no-cost products; its corporate philosophy emphasizes making a difference in the world by&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;supporting respected non-profit organizations such as Samaritan&amp;rsquo;s Purse and World Vision through&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;regular financial support. The privately-held company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more &lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;information about Liferay, please visit www.Liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;# # # #&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731204100, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4002, 4003, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3013', 1.0, 'PR-Pramati', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;h1 class=\"epi-fontLg bwtextaligncenter\" align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Teams With Pramati To Multiply Product Capability and Value&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=\"story_subheadline\"&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Integrated App Server and Portal Smoothes Path to SOA&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=\"bwtextaligncenter\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!---------- END MULTIMEDIA BOX ----------&gt;&lt;!---------- START STORY BODY ----------&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SAN FRANCISCO--(BUSINESS WIRE)&lt;/strong&gt;--Liferay, provider of the leading enterprise-class open source portal platform, and Pramati Technologies, a leading vendor of J2EE application servers and solutions, today announced a non-exclusive partnership to help customers leverage the benefits of Liferay&lt;span id=\"bwanpa2\"&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;s SOA-enabled enterprise portal framework. Under the agreement, Liferay Portal and Pramati Server will become available in a bundled version as a download on both companies&lt;span id=\"bwanpa3\"&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt; Web sites and ship with a 30-day developer license.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;quot;Bundling Liferay Portal with Pramati&lt;span id=\"bwanpa4\"&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;s robust application server software allows our customers to multiply the value and capability of their IT initiatives by leveraging Liferay&lt;span id=\"bwanpa5\"&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;s excellent user management, CMS, authentication and presentation layer capabilities,&lt;span id=\"bwanpa6\"&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt; said Jay Pullur, Founder and CEO, Pramati Technologies.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;quot;This package is timely indeed as the coming version 4.2 of Liferay Portal provides standard integration with ServiceMix ESB and the jBPM workflow engine,&amp;quot; said Brian Chan, founder and chief software architect of Liferay. &lt;span id=\"bwanpa7\"&gt;&amp;ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;These technologies allow enterprises to quickly plug in applications such as business intelligence, enterprise content management, CRM, and eCommerce on top of Pramati, which is designed to deliver complex integrated applications with high availability and scalability.&lt;span id=\"bwanpa8\"&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;Pramati expects the bundle to help its customers effortlessly build SOA capabilities into their IT infrastructure. Liferay Portal will also provide a unified user experience and a framework for extending that experience to all parts of the enterprise. The effortless nature of the bundle will allow companies to focus on developing core application functionality specific to the business.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;Liferay in turn through this relationship will leverage customer-driven innovation, demonstrate the viability of mixed proprietary and open source environments, and deliver on its promise to remain vendor-neutral with support for all major application servers.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;span id=\"bwanpa9\"&gt;&amp;ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;There is no reason why an enterprise should spend precious technical and financial resources on the details of integrating Pramati with Liferay, ESB and workflow, or on building the services provided by our portal framework,&lt;span id=\"bwanpa10\"&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt; Chan said. &lt;span id=\"bwanpa11\"&gt;&amp;ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;We want our customers to focus their efforts on building functionality that will enhance and sustain the core competitive advantages of their business.&lt;span id=\"bwanpa12\"&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;Pullur said, &lt;span id=\"bwanpa13\"&gt;&amp;ldquo;&lt;/span&gt;Analysts predict 80% of IT spending will be on SOA initiatives within two years. This only makes sense because the benefit of a well-executed SOA, an IT infrastructure that can respond quickly to rapidly changing business realities, is enormous. The Pramati / Liferay bundle will not only ensure that our customers won&lt;span id=\"bwanpa14\"&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;t be stalled in implementing an SOA; it will give them a significant lead on competitors with extremely low costs of ownership.&lt;span id=\"bwanpa15\"&gt;&amp;rdquo;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&lt;span id=\"bwanpa16\"&gt;&amp;rsquo;&lt;/span&gt;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit &lt;a target=\"_blank\" shape=\"rect\" href=\"../../../../../\"&gt;www.Liferay.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Pramati&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pramati Technologies is a leading J2EE product and services vendor. The award-winning Pramati Server is fast, robust, easy to manage and OEM licensed by ISVs. Pramati Software Services offers outsourced/off-shore product development, aftermarket services and consulting. By partnering with Pramati, our numerous satisfied customers, have enjoyed faster time to market, lower engineering expenses, and superior product performance. For more information, visit &lt;a target=\"_blank\" shape=\"rect\" href=\"http://www.pramati.com/\"&gt;www.pramati.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;Contact:&lt;/em&gt; &lt;pre&gt;LIFERAY&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=\"mailto:cgutwillig@sspr.com\"&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;847-415-9333&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;or&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;PRAMATI&lt;br /&gt;Chandrashekar Sivaram&lt;br /&gt;Hyderabad, INDIA&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=\"mailto:chandra@pramati.com\"&gt;chandra@pramati.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;+91 (40) 23411672&lt;br /&gt;or&lt;br /&gt;Vijay Prasanna Pullur&lt;br /&gt;San Jose, USA&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=\"mailto:vijay@pramati.com\"&gt;vijay@pramati.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;408-435-2700&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20061031173200, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4004, 4005, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3017', 1.0, 'PR-EDIC1', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employers Direct Insurance Company Creates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Higher Customer Satisfaction, Lower Costs with Liferay Portal&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Open Source Solution Drives Multiple Websites and Simplifies Content Management&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Duties for California&amp;rsquo;s Workers&amp;rsquo; Compensation Specialist&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AGOURA HILLS, CA &amp;ndash; (November 1, 2006) &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; Liferay, a leading provider of enterprise-class open source software products, today announced that its Liferay Portal 4.1.1 technology is powering the corporate website for Employers Direct Insurance Company, California&amp;rsquo;s only specialty direct writer of workers&amp;rsquo; compensation insurance. The site leverages Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s Web publishing, document management, authentication and user management capabilities to directly impact customer experience, lower insurance premiums, and improve Employers Direct&amp;rsquo;s bottom line.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Employers Direct eliminates costs from its sales channel by selling insurance directly to California business and industry with no independent agent or broker. This streamlined business model, in conjunction with customized loss control tools and training and fraud prevention techniques, helps lower the cost of workers&amp;rsquo; comp insurance for its policyholder customers.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Because cost and efficiency are critical to its business, Employers Direct chose to leverage the Internet to create value for its customers and to lower its administrative overhead. The company invites prospects to use the Web to determine if they qualify. In order to benefit from such an IT investment without disrupting its business model, however, Employers Direct recognized that the new site would have to be robust, easy-to-maintain, and developed with minimal cost. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Employers Direct found exactly what its solution in Liferay. Liferay&amp;rsquo;s open source license allowed Employers Direct to enjoy an immediate return on investment, faster development cycles, and the freedom to customize the product. An elegant, easy-to-use interface and powerful feature set ensured that maintenance costs would not eclipse the savings gained from the no-cost license.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;According to Greg Schueman, Vice President and Chief Information Officer for Employers Direct, Liferay Portal was the clear choice for its new technology platform. &amp;ldquo;We currently have 75 pages, 160 articles, and four custom portlets on our core website, EmployersDirect.com. In the past, this would have required huge amounts of work from programmers to establish and maintain. Liferay gave us almost all of the functionality we needed out of the box. Its web publishing system is simple enough that non-programmers can handle most of the work, which allows us to achieve our goal of having original content creators do as much ongoing content maintenance as possible.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Employers Direct was so pleased with the new platform that its customer-focused Internet-based services are just the beginning. The insurance provider is currently enhancing its Policyholder Extranet with a more extensive version of its information center, PCIC (Policyholder Claims and Information Center), that will allow companies to interact with Employers Direct and to view policy and claims-related information online. In addition, they will also be able to report a claim and connect to medical provider network (MPN) resources. The password-protected Extranet will leverage Liferay&amp;rsquo;s authentication and user management features to minimize routine phone calls between claims examiners and policyholders to simplify the entire claims reporting process.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay was extensively involved in the creation of the initial portal infrastructure and will continue to work closely with Employers Direct to build further functionality to address its business needs,&amp;rdquo; said Heather Swaim, Director of Operations for Liferay. &amp;ldquo;As Employers Direct&amp;rsquo;s web presence grows, the company will be able to offer many online services to enhance customer satisfaction while driving unnecessary administrative costs from the system.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal has become deeply embedded in our business,&amp;rdquo; stated Schueman. &amp;ldquo;Employers Direct made a strategic choice to bring much of its customer service and interaction on the Internet, which made Liferay Portal a critical element for us. We feel that we have made the right choice due to Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s ease of use and its ability to support virtually any feature or technology that we wish to deploy.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;For a full description of Liferay Portal or for an online demonstration of Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s capabilities, visit &lt;a href=\"http://www.liferay.com\"&gt;www.liferay.com&lt;/a&gt;. To view Employers Direct&amp;rsquo;s site, visit &lt;a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.employersdirect.com\"&gt;www.employersdirect.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About LIFERAY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;About EMPLOYERS DIRECT INSURANCE COMPANY:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Employers Direct Insurance Company is California\'s only specialty direct writer of workers&amp;rsquo; compensation insurance.&amp;nbsp; Founded in 2002, Employers Direct has been widely accepted by business owners throughout California as a result of providing highly competitive rates, claims services designed to fight fraud and abuse, and loss prevention services that assist employers to create safe work environments. As a newer company, Employers Direct takes advantage of the latest technology to provide its customers with 24/7 access to all policy and claims information via a secure Internet portal. Niche industries include hotels, restaurants, golf and country clubs, new car dealers, food processors, manufacturing companies, specialty supermarket chains, and retailers.&amp;nbsp; At the end of 2005, Employers Direct Insurance Company had more than $150 million in written workers&amp;rsquo; compensation premiums.&amp;nbsp; Online at www.employersdirect.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;# # #&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;&lt;font face=\"Arial\" size=\"3\"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;font size=\"2\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;LIFERAY&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;br /&gt;847-415-9333&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;or&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Employers Direct Insurance Company&lt;br /&gt;Debbie Laskey, PR Manager&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;818-575-2709&lt;br /&gt;dlaskey@employersdirect.com&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731215400, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4006, 4007, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3021', 1.0, 'PR-HanseMerkur', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Portal Provides Open Source Content Management And Services To Major German Insurer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Specialists Create Large Consumer Site with Over 350 Pages of Content for Insurer HanseMerkur Under Tight Time Constraint; Search Engine Results Improved&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;HAMBURG, GERMANY&amp;nbsp; &amp;ndash; &lt;/strong&gt;Liferay, a leading provider of enterprise-class open source software products, announced today that its professional services group has implemented Liferay Portal 4.1.2 for the new public Web site of HanseMerkur, Germany&amp;rsquo;s second-oldest mutual insurance company and a major provider of health, life, travel and property insurance.&amp;nbsp; The site brings new capabilities to both HanseMerkur and its customers, at a cost far below commercially available portal and Content Management System (CMS) alternatives. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s economical open source framework provides HanseMerkur with a superior platform for ongoing development, integration and maintenance.&amp;nbsp; In addition to its improved CMS which supports over 350 pages of content, the site offers new customer features such as the ability to initiate an insurance contract online.&amp;nbsp; An improved Search Engine Optimization (SEO) technology also leverages changes in content in real time, thereby increasing the incidence of search engine hits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;HanseMerkur&amp;rsquo;s initiative for an improved Web presence began in early 2006.&amp;nbsp; According to the company&amp;rsquo;s director of research and development, Dr. Horst Karaschewski, the company wished to dramatically increase the amount of information available online to prospective customers.&amp;nbsp; HanseMerkur envisioned its site populated with marketing content in mixed formats like HTML, graphics and PDF. Visitors to the site would interact with online content including contracts, job applications and downloadable forms. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;We looked at portal development tools from several commercial and open source providers,&amp;rdquo; noted Karaschewski.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;We were attracted to Liferay&amp;rsquo;s advanced features, ease of use, and its CMS&amp;rsquo; ability to handle extensive amounts of content.&amp;nbsp; After meeting with Liferay representatives at the CeBIT tradeshow last March, we actually expanded our proof of concept to take advantage of Liferay&amp;rsquo;s superior list of features.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay&amp;rsquo;s CMS enables HanseMerkur to organize and present its online material in an easy to maintain system,&amp;rdquo; added Suresh Shamanna, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s director of European operations.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;The client&amp;rsquo;s design team was impressed with Liferay&amp;rsquo;s flexibility in dynamically integrating external applications and internal content.&amp;rdquo; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay&amp;rsquo;s European professional services team completed construction of the new site under a demanding two-month deadline.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;Liferay&amp;rsquo;s turnaround on our project was exceptional.&amp;nbsp; The consulting team was highly motivated and delivered the resources and expertise we needed to get the job done correctly and on time,&amp;rdquo; said Karaschewski.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;Whenever changes were required, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s staff was able to accommodate them.&amp;nbsp; The end result is a quality site and a working relationship that will support HanseMerkur&amp;rsquo;s future needs.&amp;rdquo; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;During HanseMerkur&amp;rsquo;s collaboration with Liferay&amp;rsquo;s consultants, the company chose to sponsor a new Search Engine Optimization (SEO) feature to be implemented as a standard into Liferay&amp;rsquo;s coming 4.2 release.&amp;nbsp; With this new feature, HanseMerkur&amp;rsquo;s new site and Liferay Portal 4.2 can automatically and dynamically optimize its visibility on leading Web search engines.&amp;nbsp; SEO ensures that the buying public is drawn in with site information updates and keeps the HanseMerkur brand in the forefront of consumers&amp;rsquo; minds. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;HanseMerkur plans to continue working closely with the Liferay team for further enhancements and feature build-outs in the coming months.&amp;nbsp; For a full description of Liferay Portal, or for an online demonstration of Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s capabilities, please visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles.&amp;nbsp; For more information, please visit www.liferay.com&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About HanseMerkur:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;HanseMerkur is a Hamburg-based insurance group with more than 130 years of experience in private health insurance. The company, which is also Germany\'s third-biggest travel insurer, offers the whole range of life, casualty, property, accident and motor insurance. With gross premiums written of 671 million EUR in 2005, HanseMerkur\'s investment portfolio registered at an estimated 3 billion EUR last year. For further information, please visit www.hansemerkur.de.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;# # # #&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PRESS CONTACT:&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;847/955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731220600, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4008, 4009, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3025', 1.0, 'PR-EContent100', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Breaks Into EContent Magazine\'s \'\'EContent 100\'\' Of Industry Leaders&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Listing Cites Companies that &amp;quot;Matter Most in the Digital Content Industry&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES--(BUSINESS WIRE)--&lt;/strong&gt;Liferay, provider of the world\'s leading enterprise-class, open source portal and content management system, announced today that it has been named to the &amp;quot;EContent 100,&amp;quot; EContent magazine\'s list of the 100 most influential and innovative companies in the digital content industry. The list, assembled by the editors and staff of EContent magazine, includes such world-renowned software, Internet and publishing companies as Adobe Systems, Bloomberg, Google, IBM, Yahoo!, and Microsoft.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The EContent 100 ranks companies by their impact on the digital content industry. According to Michelle Manafy, editor of EContent, the companies selected are those that demonstrate &amp;quot;how far econtent reaches into our work and our lives and how the tools to make the most of it matter more than ever.&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Unlike many other industry accolades, companies may not nominate themselves for inclusion in the EContent 100. EContent magazine\'s professional staff members generate their own lists, which are then debated and ultimately assembled into the one hundred finalists.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The award recognizes Liferay\'s broad CMS offerings, including Liferay Journal, a structured web publishing system that delivers high-traffic sites such as www.csmonitor.com and www.theo2.co.uk. Liferay also ships with Document Library, which stores documents and additional information such as version, author and publication date to help an enterprise collaborate on its information assets. WebDAV makes it easy to work with these documents in the portal like Windows files.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Among the many companies and organizations now using Liferay Portal and CMS are Goodwill Industries International, Discovery Communications, British Telecom, O2, AutoZone, Bangkok Airways and the Christian Science Monitor.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;quot;From its inception, Liferay held a vision that companies and organizations of all sizes would be receptive to an integrated portal, web publishing, and content management solution that would lower costs, increase ease of development, and leverage the latest in technology,&amp;quot; said Chan. &amp;quot;We wish to thank the editors and staff of EContent magazine for recognizing our efforts.&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world\'s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;###&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731221200, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4010, 4011, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3029', 1.0, 'PR-CEO_07', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Names New CEO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Former Director of Business Development, Bryan Cheung, Takes Business Lead&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES--(BUSINESS WIRE)--&lt;/strong&gt;Liferay, provider of the world\'s leading enterprise-class, open source portal and content management system, announced that Bryan Cheung, the company\'s former Director of Business Development, has been named Chief Executive Officer. In his new role, Cheung will focus on strategic direction and expansion of Liferay Portal\'s US and international adoption. He continues to work alongside Liferay\'s creator and former CEO, Brian Chan, who now takes the title of Chief Software Architect to focus his leadership on Liferay\'s technological innovation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cheung is one of the original founding partners of Liferay, with an extensive background in both portal technology and professional services. Under his former role as Director of Business Development, Cheung helped build key business relationships with the substantial community of companies and individuals using Liferay in the U.S. and abroad. His efforts recently yielded a new German subsidiary created to meet the growing demand for Liferay professional services in Europe.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;quot;Bryan has proven his effectiveness in directing many of the most critical business affairs of this company,&amp;quot; said Brian Chan. &amp;quot;His work already encompassed many senior duties including alliances, business development and market strategy. Most importantly, Bryan and I share in Liferay\'s vision to make an impact on the world, and I believe he will be even more effective in doing so in his new role.&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;quot;Liferay has an amazing team of developers under Brian Chan\'s thought leadership, and this change will give him the freedom to focus on product development,&amp;quot; said Cheung. &amp;quot;Meanwhile, we will continue to leverage our position as the open source portal leader to foster innovation and offer real value through our professional services team.&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Cheung\'s appointment offers a fitting end to a year of significant organizational growth and development for Liferay. The company shifted from LLC to corporation status in 2006; it formalized its Germany subsidiary; it extended strategic alliances to include partners such as Alfresco and Virtuas Open Source Solutions, among others; and took its flagship product to version 4.2.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Bryan Cheung graduated from the University of California, Berkeley with a Bachelor\'s in Computer Science.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is the world\'s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;###&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Contact:&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/p&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731221700, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4012, 4013, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3033', 1.0, 'PR-Liferay_Germany', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Opens German Office To Service European Demand For Web Portal Software&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Company Responds to Strong Adoption Rate Among European Enterprise Users&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LANGEN, GERMANY&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash;&amp;nbsp; Liferay, provider of the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal and content management system, today announced the opening of a European headquarters in Germany to serve the professional services needs of enterprise customers throughout continental Europe and the United Kingdom. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay&amp;rsquo;s new European office, located at Siemens Straße 6F in Langen, Germany, began operations in October, 2006.&amp;nbsp; The office is a key component of Liferay&amp;rsquo;s plan to aggressively expand its services to enterprise customers outside of North America.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay is fast becoming a global standard for enterprise-class portal development and content management,&amp;rdquo; said Suresh Shamanna, director of European operations and head of Liferay&amp;rsquo;s European headquarters.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;Our company is experiencing a significant upswing in demand for development, services and training around our products, particularly in Germany and the broader European community.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Shamanna added that Liferay Europe has already implemented several significant projects, including its ongoing work at HanseMerkur, Germany&amp;rsquo;s second oldest insurance company. The company also counts major European enterprises such as o2, Vodaphone and some of Europe&amp;rsquo;s largest financial institutions as users of its products. &amp;ldquo;Liferay has been in use by European enterprises for several years and a strong user community exists here,&amp;rdquo; he noted.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;Our new office provides these enterprises with the benefit of local&amp;ndash;language professional support and direct access to Liferay&amp;rsquo;s international development and professional services teams.&amp;rdquo; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s flagship open source product, has proven popular in Europe for its maturity, strong support for standards, a liberal MIT license, and robust internationalization features. A service oriented architecture and enterprise integration tools such as Liferay ServiceBuilder have helped Liferay make inroads to Fortune Global 100 companies against competitors such as IBM Websphere Portal, JBoss Portal and BEA WebLogic Portal.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay will be exhibiting at the CeBIT technology trade show, March 15-21, 2007 in Hannover, Germany.&amp;nbsp; For more information about Liferay Europe, contact the company&amp;rsquo;s European headquarters at +49-06103-928336, or visit www.liferay.com.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;####&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;Contact:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731222100, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4014, 4015, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3037', 1.0, 'PR-InfoWorld07_Award', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Portal Wins InfoWorld&amp;rsquo;s&lt;br /&gt;2007 Technology Of The Year Award&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Version 4.0 Named &amp;ldquo;Best Open Source Portal&amp;rdquo; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES, CA &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; (February 1, 2007) &amp;ndash; Liferay, provider of the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal, today announced that Liferay Portal 4.0 has earned a 2007 Technology of the Year award from InfoWorld magazine, one of the IT industry&amp;rsquo;s most respected trade publications. The 2007 &amp;ldquo;Technology of the Year&amp;rdquo; awards were presented to just 41 products out of hundreds evaluated while Liferay&amp;rsquo;s award for &amp;ldquo;Best Open Source Portal&amp;rdquo; was one of only four given in the Applications category.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal 4.0 rivals many commercial portal platforms in both functionality and technology,&amp;rdquo; said InfoWorld of the category winner. In fact, this has been a view long held by the publication. In a 2006 InfoWorld review, Mark Heck also affirmed the quality of the product saying, &amp;ldquo;Using Liferay Portal 4.0 was totally enjoyable. I was impressed with the solid administration, flexible deployment options, and how much functionality comes out of the box&amp;hellip;If I had to quickly create a finished portal with open source tools, Liferay would be my first choice for its usability, polished look, and supplied portlets.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal continues to grow in reputation as one of the best choices on the market for enterprise portal development,&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp; said Bryan Cheung, chief executive officer of Liferay, &amp;ldquo;We&amp;rsquo;re honored that InfoWorld magazine shares this view and will keep innovating to maintain our leadership. Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s current 4.2 version has been extremely well received and the coming 4.3 version will offer even more impressive user features and back-end functionality.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;InfoWorld magazine provides specialized IT coverage for CTOs and senior company executives with deep technology expertise and experience.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The publication provides in-depth technical analysis on key products, solutions, and technologies critical to today&amp;rsquo;s enterprises. The Technology of the Year award winners are selected by the magazine&amp;rsquo;s test editors and reviewers and were announced in the January 1, 2007 edition of InfoWorld magazine and on InfoWorld.com. Of the more than 230 products reviewed in 2006, only the &amp;ldquo;best and most innovative&amp;rdquo; products were chosen to represent their class.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;# # # # &lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731222600, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4016, 4017, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3041', 1.0, 'PR-CIGNEX_Partnership', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay-CIGNEX Form Open Source Services Partnership &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Leading Open Source Consulting Firm &lt;br /&gt;Offers Integrated ECM/Portal Solutions as Preferred Partner&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;LOS ANGELES and SANTA CLARA, CA &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; (February 7, 2007) &amp;ndash; Liferay, provider of the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal and content management system announced a new partnership with CIGNEX Technologies, a top ten open source consulting firm in the U.S. specializing in Enterprise Content Management (ECM) solutions. CIGNEX&amp;rsquo;s formalized services offering around Liferay Portal for its corporate customers underscores a growing demand for Liferay in the enterprise environment. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Commercial open source has entered a new stage of maturity,&amp;rdquo; said Bryan Cheung, chief executive officer of Liferay. &amp;ldquo;Open source has been a disruptive force in the ECM and portal marketplaces, with open source alternatives providing technological innovation, an improved development model, and greater control to users at a fraction of the cost of ownership for proprietary software. CIGNEX&amp;rsquo;s success proves the enterprise market is ready to invest in open source, and we welcome the experience CIGNEX brings to this partnership.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For CIGNEX, Liferay is the only open source portal able to address the needs of its enterprise clients. &amp;ldquo;Liferay&amp;rsquo;s offering of business-class product support behind the product is a standout differentiator in the open source space,&amp;rdquo; said Navin Nagiah, chief executive officer of CIGNEX Technologies, who also cited Liferay&amp;rsquo;s technical fit to the enterprise market. &amp;ldquo;After evaluating other products, it was clear to us that Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s agility and richness of feature set was the best match for our clients&amp;rsquo; needs. We see a lot of potential in the technology&amp;mdash;not just for ECM, but also for extensions into Customer Relationship Management, Enterprise Resource Planning and other major enterprise applications.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The partnership is also a natural progression following Liferay Portal 4.2&amp;rsquo;s delivery of out of the box integration with Alfresco. Along with Alfresco, Liferay Portal is one of two software products that CIGNEX has committed to strategically major in.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;CIGNEX provides complete open source solutions for Web content management, collaboration, document management, records management, portals, and content intelligence.&amp;nbsp; It uses a limited and highly select set of best-of-breed enterprise products for its projects deployed in a wide range of industries; among its more notable clients are Cisco, Eli Lilly, Epson, HP, Hyperion, UNC Healthcare, and the University of California.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With today&amp;rsquo;s announcement, CIGNEX becomes the first U.S.&amp;ndash;based member of Liferay&amp;rsquo;s Preferred Partner program.&amp;nbsp; In addition to sharing business activities, the two companies will work together to provide thought leadership and innovation to the open source ECM/portal software community. CIGNEX associates will be fully and regularly trained in Liferay Portal technology, while CIGNEX will serve as a reseller of Liferay&amp;rsquo;s enterprise support services. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay and CIGNEX are already collaborating on several corporate projects.&amp;nbsp; For more about Liferay Portal, visit www.liferay.com.&amp;nbsp; Additional information about CIGNEX can be found at www.cignex.com.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. Liferay clients include Discovery Education, Goodwill Industries, and the Christian Science Monitor. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About CIGNEX Technologies: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;CIGNEX is the leading provider of open source Enterprise Content Management solutions for businesses and government agencies.&amp;nbsp; Using industry-standard platforms, CIGNEX develops applications that are less expensive, more extensible, and easier to support than the alternatives offered by proprietary vendors.&amp;nbsp; By combining a range of consulting, development, training, support and ongoing maintenance services, CIGNEX offers multiple solutions that can be rapidly optimized for each customer&amp;rsquo;s requirements.&amp;nbsp; CIGNEX customers include Lawrence Livermore National Laboratories, Epson Electronics America, University of North Carolina Healthcare, University of North Carolina School of Medicine and OKI Semiconductor.&amp;nbsp; CIGNEX was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in Santa Clara, CA.&amp;nbsp; For additional information about CIGNEX please visit http://www.CIGNEX.com or call 408.327.9900.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;####&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731223100, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4018, 4019, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3045', 1.0, 'PR-Liferay_Trivir_Brainshare', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Partners with TriVir, Novell Experts &lt;br /&gt;Offer Portal Alternative for the Enterprise&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Co-exhibiting at Novell Brainshare 2007&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES--(BUSINESS WIRE)--&lt;/strong&gt;Liferay, provider of the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal and content management system announced a new partnership with TriVir, a company of seasoned Novell alumni majoring in portal services and identity management. The relationship was formed to offer Liferay Portal as a compelling alternative for enterprise users.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;With Novell dropping support for its exteNd Director portal product in 2009, many Novell enterprise customers in need of a portal solution are looking for new options with long-term viability. TriVir approached Liferay, its preferred portal platform, to build dedicated solutions for this audience in a Novell environment as an exteNd replacement. Said Britt Courtney, co-founder of TriVir, &amp;ldquo;Looking at our customers and the market potential for Novell integrated solutions our best long term strategy has always contained Liferay as a component of a competitive, flexible and long lasting technology stack. Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s maturity on the market, its growing community of Novell users and compatibility with Novell products made it our platform of choice for creating a viable replacement for Novell exteNd.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;This partnership with TriVir couldn&amp;rsquo;t have come at a better time,&amp;rdquo; said Liferay CEO, Bryan Cheung. &amp;ldquo;TriVir&amp;rsquo;s expertise in identity management and Novell technology will be a great asset in meeting the demand we see from the enterprise market. It has already yielded enhanced integration with Novell and could result in even a full- blown Liferay Portal Novell Edition.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The companies will debut several of the developments at this year&amp;rsquo;s Novell Brainshare conference in Salt Lake City Utah. There, Liferay\'s chief software architect Brian Chan and CTO Mike Young (Booth 230) will demonstrate how to deploy a full open source stack using Novell SUSE Linux 10, Apache Geronimo Application Server 1.1, and Liferay Portal. Key features of the portal and a high level objective comparison with other offerings will be highlighted so that attendees who provide Novell professional services can make informed recommendations to clients.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Additionally, TriVir (Booth 530) will showcase new features of a &amp;quot;Novell Enabled&amp;quot; Liferay portal, including:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay running behind Access Manager &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; TriVir has created code that will deliver a nice, neat single sign on feature. The security for Novell\'s Access Manager 3.0 works with a number of popular application servers, making this a good fit for many Novell users.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PasswordSmith portlet &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; The first eDirectory Universal Password-enabled JSR-168 Portlet developed by TriVir. Simply drop it into an existing portal environment. The real power of this feature is that it is written to leverage password policies and Universal Password from eDirectory.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Subscription portlet &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; TriVir&amp;rsquo;s custom portlet that allows users to subscribe to newsletters based upon the business unit, or LDAP organizational unit.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Novell Identity Management integration&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; with Liferay via the Liferay web service interface.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Innovations to come include a Novell IDM 3.5 enabled Liferay portal and other custom portal tools. &amp;ldquo;The investment around Liferay is in line with the requests and needs of our market,&amp;rdquo; said Courtney. &amp;ldquo;We look forward to showcasing some of the interesting new technologies being developed through this new partnership at Brainshare.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. Liferay clients include Discovery Education, Goodwill Industries, and the Christian Science Monitor. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About TriVir:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;TriVir, LLC was founded in 2003 by a small group of former Novell consultants and engineers. These tried and tested professionals have many years of experience in delivering proven, real-world solutions. This experience has given them a deep understanding of networks and network-associated technologies.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;This background in real-world experience allows TriVir to deliver practical solutions that can transform a complex maze of cables and machinery into an easy-to-use, secure computing network.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;TriVir\'s goal is to reduce maintenance requirements and cut administrative costs for all clients through effective design and thoughtful planning. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;em&gt;####&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731223600, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4020, 4021, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3049', 1.0, 'PR-NovellTeaming', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Novell Teaming + Conferencing Uses Liferay Portal&lt;br /&gt;As its Default Portal Platform&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Collaboration Offering Built on SiteScape&amp;rsquo;s New ICEcorps Product &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SALT LAKE CITY, UTAH &amp;ndash; (April 2, 2007) &amp;ndash;&lt;/strong&gt; Liferay Portal, the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal, was demoed as the default platform for the new Novell Teaming + Conferencing collaboration product during a morning keynote at the 2007 Novell BrainShare conference.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Novell Teaming + Conferencing is based on SiteScape&amp;rsquo;s new ICEcorps open source collaboration product and allows employees to use virtual workspaces to share and access documents, calendars, discussion forums, and to convene real-time Web conferences. Built for the enterprise, Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s impressive out-of-the-box collaboration tools and the maturity of its technology made it a fitting platform for Novell Teaming + Conferencing and ICEcorps. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay was an obvious choice for ICEcorps because of its maturity and scalability,&amp;rdquo; said Andy Fox, SiteScape&amp;rsquo;s Chief Technical Officer. &amp;ldquo;We are excited about the opportunity to involve the Liferay community in our project.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Also, unlike other proprietary portal solutions, Liferay Portal can run on any application server, database server and operating system. &amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal does not limit SiteScape&amp;rsquo;s ICEcorps audience to any particular technology stack&amp;rdquo;, added Fox. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Said, Brian Chan, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s Chief Software Architect, &amp;ldquo;Using Liferay ensures that existing technology investments do not have to be jettisoned and that future changes will not require an overhaul of your portal solution. Liferay Portal was created with long-term interoperability in mind and we are thrilled that Novell Teaming + Conferencing and Sitescape users will enjoy the enduring benefits of using our technology. We look forward to seeing more of SiteScape&amp;rsquo;s involvement in our community.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. Liferay clients include Discovery Education, Goodwill Industries, and the Christian Science Monitor. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;# # # #&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div align=\"left\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731224300, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4022, 4023, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3053', 1.0, 'PR-Novell Market Start', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font size=\"2\"&gt;Liferay Partners With Novell&lt;/font&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Provides Enterprise-Class Solutions to SMBs as &lt;br /&gt;Part of Novell Market Start&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;LOS ANGELES, CA &amp;ndash; (BUSINESS WIRE)&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; Liferay, provider of the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal and content management system today announced its participation in Novell Market Start.&amp;nbsp; The Market Start program offers small and medium businesses (SMBs) enterprise-class solutions with easier deployments and at a fraction of the cost.&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;Liferay&amp;rsquo;s membership in Novell Market Start makes a lot of sense given the existing overlap in our user bases,&amp;rdquo; said Liferay CEO, Bryan Cheung. &amp;ldquo;Liferay Portal is equipped with the tools and technology to address the needs of a large enterprise but our open source licensing brings us significant popularity among smaller organizations as well.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Offered under the business friendly MIT license, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s portal framework and over 60 prebundled tools, including a built-in content management system and full suite of collaboration tools, can be downloaded at no cost and reworked or re-packaged with no legal repercussions. Moreover, Liferay Portal allows organizations with limited resources to avoid overhauls of existing IT investments as it is the only open source portal that is compatible with all major application servers, databases and operating systems. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;Liferay offers our customers and partners&amp;nbsp; a wide collection of enterprise-class portal tools and the option to customize them as their business grows.&amp;rdquo;&amp;nbsp; said Justin Steinman, director of marketing for Linux and Open Platform Solutions atNovell. While Liferay is certified Ready for for SUSE Linux Enterprise, Liferay also offers out-of-the-box integration with key Novell products such as Novell eDirectory and Novell Identity Manager along with Novell-specific security-related tools.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;Added Cheung, &amp;ldquo;The beauty of open source is that the quality of your IT and business processes is no longer determined by your size. It makes the playing field more competitive and gives management room to focus on growth. This is one of the main reasons that Liferay is pleased to be selected for&amp;nbsp; Novell Market Start.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;For more about Liferay Portal and the coming version 4.3, visit &lt;a href=\"http://www.liferay.com\"&gt;www.liferay.com&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp; Additional information about Novell Market Start can be found at www.novell.com/linux/marketstart.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. Liferay clients include Discovery Education, Goodwill Industries, and the Christian Science Monitor. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit &lt;a href=\"http://www.liferay.com\"&gt;www.liferay.com&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;# # # #&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Press Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/p&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731224900, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
insert into JournalArticle (id_, resourcePrimKey, groupId, companyId, userId, userName, createDate, modifiedDate, articleId, version, title, description, content, type_, structureId, templateId, displayDate, approved, approvedByUserId, approvedByUserName, expired, indexable) values (4024, 4025, 14, 1, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, '3057', 1.0, 'PR-Liferay 4.3', '', '<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n\n<root default-locale=\"en_US\" available-locales=\"en_US\">\n  <dynamic-element name=\"content\" type=\"text_area\">\n    <dynamic-content language-id=\"en_US\">&lt;div align=\"justify\"&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liferay Portal 4.3 Now Available&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Latest Release Further Enhances Usability and Performance&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LOS ANGELES &amp;ndash; (JUNE 28, 2007) &lt;/strong&gt;&amp;ndash; Liferay, provider of the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise-class, open source portal framework, today announced the release of Liferay Portal 4.3. The latest version of the award-winning portal features a revamped user interface and improvements in performance.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;In the last several months we&amp;rsquo;ve focused on making our portal easier than ever to use,&amp;rdquo; said Brian Chan, Liferay&amp;rsquo;s founder and Chief Software Architect.&amp;nbsp; &amp;ldquo;Users will see a marked difference from our previous versions in the visual and interactive experience.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Among several features enhancing the user experience is Liferay Portal&amp;rsquo;s new Freeform or &amp;ldquo;WebOS&amp;rdquo; theme, which mirrors the look and feel of a standard desktop environment. Portal applications (portlets) can now be moved, layered, and resized as users wish without restriction for a more intuitive working environment. Liferay Portal 4.3 also introduces the Web 2.0 convention of tagging, bringing user-driven content categorization to the enterprise. Administrators will welcome the reduced effort in managing content while still retaining control over how much users can do in the portal.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;An assortment of other user-centered features round out the new release, including:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Portal Publishing &amp;amp; Staging &lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; Staging allows administrators to preview changes to portal pages before publishing those changes to a live public page.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Federated Search &lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; Liferay Portal leverages Amazon&amp;rsquo;s OpenSearch to return search results in one result set from multiple sources including Liferay portlets and external applications.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Sitemaps Protocol Support &lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; Sitemaps makes newly added pages instantaneously searcheable by all major search engines without additional configuration.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Open ID&lt;/em&gt; &amp;ndash; OpenID stores all of a user&amp;rsquo;s information in one place and provides part of it (as approved by the user) to the websites where the user wants to participate. This makes it much easier to protect user information and keep it up to date. For website owners, OpenID facilitates end user registration by negating the effort it takes to register in a website.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Multiple Enterprise Management &lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; This allows an organization to run multiple enterprise portals from just one installation of Liferay, each with its own distinct communities, branding and set up as defined by the administrators.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Mobile Device Support &lt;/em&gt;&amp;ndash; Content and pages in Liferay Portal can now be accessed via mobile devices including Blackberrys, PDAs, and mobile phones.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Technical users will also appreciate performance enhancements in the new version. Liferay Portal has been streamlined to leverage the Spring framework more deeply to eliminate the need for EJBs, and tuning of the persistence layer has further improved scalability and reduced system requirements. Liferay Portal 4.3 also adds new tools to simplify the development process:&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liferay Eclipse Plug-In&amp;mdash; Version 4.3 includes a custom-built Eclipse plug-in that speeds up portlet development by performing traditionally manual setup processes.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Liferay Software Catalog&amp;mdash;The software catalog connects to remote portlet and theme repositories, keeping track of new and updated offerings and enabling them to be instantly installed or updated without restarting the server.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;In development since 2000, Liferay is a popular platform among developers thanks to its flexible architecture and compatibility with today&amp;rsquo;s best technologies. It is being used at some of the world&amp;rsquo;s largest enterprises as a solution to a variety of business issues, ranging from data management with the built in content management system to organizational productivity and communication with Liferay&amp;rsquo;s full suite of collaboration tools.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&amp;ldquo;We drew from both client and community feedback for this release,&amp;rdquo; said Chan, &amp;ldquo;Liferay is fortunate to have such a large and active community supporting and driving innovation.&amp;rdquo;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Version 4.3 is available at no cost under the MIT license and is available for immediate download at &lt;a href=\"http://www.liferay.com/web/guest/downloads\"&gt;www.liferay.com/web/guest/downloads&lt;/a&gt;.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Liferay:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Liferay Portal is the world&amp;rsquo;s leading enterprise open source portal framework with Fortune 500 clients in the U.S. and Europe. Liferay Professional Services offers technical support, custom development and professional training to ensure successful deployment of its flagship product in the most demanding IT environments. The company is headquartered in Los Angeles. For more information, please visit www.liferay.com.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;div align=\"center\"&gt;###&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;S&amp;amp;S Public Relations, Inc.&lt;br /&gt;Corey Gutwillig, 847-955-0700 ext. 9333&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=\"mailto:cgutwillig@sspr.com\"&gt;cgutwillig@sspr.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</dynamic-content>\n  </dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'press-release', 'BASIC-CONTENT', 'BASIC-CONTENT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070731225700, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
