IT manager want included in their solution? Answer that question, and you could win $1000.<br /><br /><strong>Best Integration/Mashup Portlet</strong><br />Create a portlet that integrates with a third-party application such as MS Exchange or CRM. Examples include the Google Map integration already within FireScope.<br /><br /><strong>$500 Most Entertaining Portlet</strong><br />Use your imagination and create a fun portlet that can be entertaining and engaging for users of all levels.<br /><br /><strong>$500 Best Concept</strong><br />This award goes to the overall best concept. Whether it accommodates the needs of an enterprise or incorporates a third party as a mashup (or both!) &ndash; this award will be given to the portlet with the most original use and content. <br /><br /><strong><br />CONTEST RULES:</strong><br />Submitted portlets can be written in Java, PHP or Ruby, and MUST be able to run on Liferay 4.3!<br />Check out Liferay for detailed development documentation and other resources.<br /><br />Submit your portlets to <a href=\"mailto:portletcontest@firescope.com?subject=Portlet%20Contest\">portletcontest@firescope.com</a> in a zipped file. Make sure to read the Porlet Contest Rules and sign the waiver before entering.<br /><br /><br /><br /><strong>ABOUT FIRESCOPE:</strong><br /><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.firescope.com\">FireScope, Inc.</a> offers a single solution that provides a real-time view of the health of IT operations by collecting and processing security, performance and availability data from nearly any server, router, security point solution or other networked device. It&rsquo;s built from multiple industry-proven open-source programs and integrated into an easy to use, Web-based dashboard. Solution options range from 20 monitored devices to thousands, making FireScope a product that can be tailored for businesses of any size. FireScope, Inc. is headquartered in Huntington Beach, California, and provides organizations with actionable business intelligence concerning the health and security of all critical IT assets, regardless of operating system or platform with its FireScope line of security appliances.<br /><em><br />Products at a glance</em>:<br />The FireScope line of IT Operations Management appliances represent a new way to approach effective security. By blending the best open source technology with an intuitive user interface, FireScope delivers actionable business intelligence about your infrastructure without the need to consult multiple security point applications and raw system logs.<br /><br />For more information about how Firescope uses Liferay, please email <a href=\"mailto:events@liferay.com?subject=Portlet%20Design%20Contest\">events@liferay.com</a>.</p>]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"open-header-link-in-new-window\" type=\"boolean\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[false]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"image-link\" type=\"text\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n	<dynamic-element name=\"open-image-link-in-new-window\" type=\"boolean\">\n		<dynamic-content><![CDATA[false]]></dynamic-content>\n	</dynamic-element>\n</root>', 'general', 'BASIC-ARTICLE', 'BASIC-IMAGE-TEXT', SPECIFIC_TIMESTAMP_20070808210100, TRUE, 2, 'Joe Bloggs', FALSE, TRUE);
